The paper deals with a problem in information theory (group testing) and proposes a framework based on sparse graph codes. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for decoding and grouping subsets of items efficiently. The use of sparse graph codes also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed framework, which may fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
